    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-18T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-18T09:00:00-05:00" n="797"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d797">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.796/253: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Burdett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-18T11:00:00-03:00"
                            >November 18, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 18—9:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>594. As a result of crash last week the President of the Vasp Airline has
                    requested the Embassy’s assistance in facilitating the purchase <pb facs="0680"
                        n="668" xml:id="pg_668"/> and delivery of three Douglas DC–3 airplanes; two
                    for delivery within 45 days. Gates and Hardin were present at the interview. The
                    Embassy gave Vasp no assurances except the promise that the Department would be
                    informed by telegraph. The Vasp is in touch with the local agent of Douglas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Burdett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
